{"article_id":"khPW78pjipSqtKVv","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Former coronavirus patients like actor Daniel Dae Kim swear by it ,","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"but","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"even after receiving emergency FDA approval ,","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"the anti-malarial drug hydroxychloroquine still has an image problem on the left","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"after being touted by President Trump .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"The FDA issued an emergency-use authorization late Sunday for chloroquine and its next-generation version , hydroxychloroquine , as treatments for the novel coronavirus ,","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"fueling the political back-and-forth","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"that erupted March 19","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"when Mr. Trump called hydroxychloroquine a potential \" game changer .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"\" \" I don ' t understand","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"how the FDA can approve anti-malaria drugs chloroquine and hydroxychloroquine for the coronavirus","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"without any reputable clinical trials","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"proving","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"that they work , \"","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"tweeted Dr. Eugene Gu , an outspoken Trump social media critic .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"\" FDA decided to use human beings as guinea pigs","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"based on anecdotal reports and advice from Dr. Trump . \"","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"After Twitter removed Monday a post by Fox host Laura Ingraham","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"highlighting one doctor ' s success with hydroxychloroquine ,","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"conservatives erupted ,","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"with some calling the drug ' s opponents \" deniers . \"","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"\" Because Trump mentioned it as a potential treatment ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"expect the Hydroxychloroquine-deniers in the media to furiously report on any , & EVERY , negative interaction or non-therapeutic result , \"","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"tweeted the Bongino Report ' s Dan Bongino .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"\" Essentially creating a new standard for pharmaceutical reporting","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"applying only to this drug . \"","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"Conservative pundit Ben Shapiro tweeted ,","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"\" So it ' s a no on ' hydroxychloroquine is a promising treatment '","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"but yes on the Chinese government","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"claiming","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that coronavirus originated in the US .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Just to get this straight , @ jack , \"","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"referring to Twitter CEO Jack Dorsey .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"The drugs ,","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"which are FDA-approved for malaria , lupus and rheumatoid arthritis ,","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"have been used","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"to treat coronavirus patients in Belgium , China and South Korea .","depth":4},{"id":37,"text":"U.S. medical centers have increasingly added hydroxychloroquine off-label to their treatment protocols in combination with azithromycin ,","depth":4},{"id":38,"text":"while New York has begun clinical trials .","depth":4},{"id":39,"text":"Still , aside from a small study out of France","depth":6},{"id":40,"text":"that showed promising results ,","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"information on the drug ' s impact on COVID-19 is mainly anecdotal ,","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"in large part because the virus is too new","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"to have been extensively studied .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"Among those anecdotes is the case of Mr. Kim ,","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"who called the drug the \" secret weapon \" in his recovery .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"Jim Santilli , CEO of the Transportation Improvement Association , said","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"that the drug combination \" saved my life \"","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"after he was hospitalized with COVID-19 .","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"\" It was a struggle to breathe","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"and I felt like I was slowly drowning , \"","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"tweeted Mr. Santilli .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"\" Luckily , the doctors decided to try Hydroxychloroquine and Azithromycin .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Within a few hours , the gasping for air stopped","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"and I began improving .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"I went home 3 days later ! \"","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Only time will tell","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"whether the drugs are effective","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"in treating in COVID-19 ,","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"but the skeptical tenor of the mainstream media coverage is already evident .","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"In a March 21 editorial , the USA Today editorial board declared ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"\" Dr . Donald Trump peddles snake oil and false hope , \"","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"while CNN article challenged the president ' s claims in an article","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"headlined ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"\" Trump peddles unsubstantiated hope in dark times . \"","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"Bloomberg News followed up with","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"\" Malaria drug no better than regular coronavirus care , study finds , \"","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"even though the study","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"published by the Journal of Zhejiang University in China","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"involved only 30 patients","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"and the results \" weren ' t statistically significant , \"","depth":13},{"id":71,"text":"as the March 24 article admitted .","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"\" The sound of it seems to be ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"' Let ' s deny him","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"[ Trump ]","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"a victory , ' \"","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"said Tim Graham , director of media analysis for the conservative Media Research Center .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"\" If there ' s a light going on at the end of the tunnel ,","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"we need to smash the light to bits ,","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"even though we should be looking for hope at his point . \"","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"Meanwhile , the progressive Media Matters for America blasted Fox News for its \" reckless speculation and endorsement \" of the drugs ,","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"accusing the network ' s personalities of \" creating a false impression of a working treatment for the deadly disease . \"","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"The outrage peaked last week","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"when an Arizona man accidentally poisoned himself","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"ingesting a chloroquine phosphate product","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"intended as fish-tank cleaner","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"to self-medicate against COVID-19 ,","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"prompting the","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"[ U.K. ]","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"Guardian headline ,","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"\" Arizona man dies","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"after attempting to take Trump coronavirus ' cure ' . \"","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Fox host Tucker Carlson said","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"after the president expressed confidence in the drug ,","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"\" That was it for the media .","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"\" If Trump is for it ,","depth":11},{"id":97,"text":"they ' re against it ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"even if it might save American lives , \"","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"said Mr. Carlson last week .","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"\" And they immediately began a sustained push","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"to discredit the drug","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"long before clinical results in . \"","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"After CNN reported Monday","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"that \" there is little scientific evidence \"","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"showing","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"that the treatments are effective ,","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"Ms. Ingraham weighed in on Twitter .","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"\" Why does CNN not recognize the COVID patients all over the world","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"who have walked out of hospitals","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"testing negative","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"after being treated with hydroxychloroquine ? \"","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"she tweeted .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":225,"left":145,"right":224,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":117,"right":144,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":117,"left":0,"right":116,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":116,"left":115,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":115,"left":1,"right":114,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":114,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":144,"left":120,"right":143,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":5,"right":119,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":6,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":127,"right":142,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":127,"left":125,"right":126,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":124,"right":14,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":121,"right":123,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":123,"left":11,"right":122,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":15,"right":16,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":135,"right":141,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"